# Module

## Uses

::READ (Construct: Tag) FROM `../expressions/tag.art`.
::READ (Construct: NaturalName) FROM `../expressions/natural-name.art`.
::READ (Construct: NaturalBlock) FROM `./natural-block.art`.

## Construct: FieldBlock

**Category:** Structural

**Purpose:** Represent a named property within a SectionBlock.

**Description:** A FieldBlock associates a name with a value within a SectionBlock. The value of the FieldBlock is the NaturalBlock that follows the field identifier, up to the next FieldBlock, FieldInline, or InlineDeclaration.

<!-- refine content rules -->

**Schema:**

```art
FieldBlock {
    name: <NaturalName>
    value: <NaturalBlock>
}
```

**Syntax:**

```art
<FieldBlock> =
    **<NaturalName (field.name)>:** [<Tag> ...]
        <NaturalBlock>
```

**Rules:**

- A FieldBlock MUST define a name.
- A FieldBlock MUST define a value.
- A FieldBlock MAY be tagged with one or more Tag.
- A FieldBlock value consists of all following content until the next FieldBlock, FieldInline, InlineDeclaration, or the end of the enclosing SectionBlock.
- A FieldBlock MAY contain arbitrary content including procedure blocks, example blocks, directives, and raw Markdown content.

**Example:**

```md
**Inputs:**

- `%task` – The task to modify.
- `%specification` – The specification to integrate into the task.
```
